criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  current experience of psychotic symptoms,

          -  meeting threshold for DP/DR disorder (scores greater than 70 on Cambridge
             Depersonalization Scale (CDS)).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  insufficient capacity to provide informed consent;

          -  insufficient proficiency in English (spoken and written) to engage in CBT;

          -  a primary diagnosis of intellectual disability, head injury, substance misuse or
             organic cause for psychosis;

          -  those currently engaging in CBT or other psychotherapy.
